abstract: National Association of Realtors reports that seasonally adjusted pending home sales index rose 3.4 percent to 112.4 in April, marking fourth consecutive monthly gain.
lead_paragraph: In April, Americans signed contracts to buy homes at the fastest pace in nearly nine years, evidence that steady job growth is strengthening the real estate market.

headline.main: U.S. Homes Go Under Contract at Fastest Pace in 9 Years
